Zandie Khumalo spoke exclusively with eNCA. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Shocking claims have emerged from an exclusive interview with Zandie Khumalo, one of the people in the house on the night football star Senzo Meyiwa was killed in 2014. Zandie has defended her sister Kelly Khumalo against persistent speculation that she may have ordered a hit on her former lover. EXCLUSIVE: Senzo Meyiwa murder | Zandie Khumalo speaks Zandie says her family and others in the house that night were subjected to hours of interrogation by police and a lie detector test. She claims that Meyiwa's wife or mother were not interrogated in this way. WATCH: Meyiwa murder | Zandie Khumalo says she was interrogated for hours She suggests the killing may have been a hit meant for Kelly, who was having an affair with the star at the time. Five men are currently on trial for the murder. READ: Meyiwa Murder Trial | Zandie Khumalo breaks her silence "Looking at this whole situation, if someone is dead and is a husband if someone the first suspect would be the girlfriend or the wife," she said. "But no one has ever looked at Mandisa. Why is she not being investigated? Is it even possible that Senzo's mother and Mandisa conspired? Why can't police look in other people, look at other possibilities?"